HIMS Relay Agent - Site Collector
==================================
Agent name : {{.AgentName}}
Site       : {{.SiteName}}
HIMS server: {{.URL}}
Version    : {{.Version}}
Package OS : {{.OSLabel}}

WHAT THIS IS
------------
The HIMS Relay Agent is a small service that runs on ONE trusted machine inside
this site. HIMS hands it collection jobs (it polls outward - no inbound firewall
rule is needed), it collects locally (modern Windows over WinRM and legacy
Windows over WMI/DCOM), and posts the results back. It is the official, supported
way to collect site-local and legacy hosts.

>> SECURITY - THIS PACKAGE IS SENSITIVE <<
This .zip contains a one-time registration TOKEN for this agent. Treat the file
like a password:
  * Copy it to the target machine over a trusted channel only.
  * Do NOT email it or leave it on shared drives.
  * Delete the package once the agent shows ONLINE in HIMS.
The package does NOT contain any device credentials. The agent never stores
credentials; HIMS sends the right credential to the agent per job, over the
authenticated channel, and the agent discards it after each job.

INSTALL (recommended - no build tools required)
-----------------------------------------------
1. Copy this whole folder to the target Windows / domain-joined machine.
2. Right-click  install.cmd  ->  "Run as administrator".
3. Confirm the prompt. The installer will:
      - copy hims-agent.exe to "Program Files\HIMS Relay Agent"
      - register a Windows service named "{{.DisplayName}}"
      - start it (Automatic start, restart-on-failure)
      - validate connectivity + registration
4. In HIMS -> Discovery -> Relay Agents, this agent appears ONLINE within ~30s.

SILENT / UNATTENDED (for IT deployment)
---------------------------------------
   install.cmd /silent
or directly:
   powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\Install-HIMSRelayAgent.ps1 -Silent

REPAIR / REINSTALL
------------------
   install.cmd /repair

UNINSTALL
---------
   install.cmd /uninstall
This stops + removes the service, clears the machine configuration, and deletes
the installed files. The agent then shows offline in HIMS.

THE WINDOWS SERVICE
-------------------
  Name        : {{.ServiceName}}  (display: "{{.DisplayName}}")
  Startup     : Automatic
  Recovery    : restart on failure (5s, 5s, then every 30s)
  Runs as     : LocalSystem
  Manage      : services.msc  (Start / Stop / Restart), or
                  sc start {{.ServiceName}}   /   sc stop {{.ServiceName}}
  Version     : run  "C:\Program Files\HIMS Relay Agent\hims-agent.exe" -version
  Logs        : C:\ProgramData\HIMS\RelayAgent\logs\agent.log

TROUBLESHOOTING
---------------
  * "token was rejected (HTTP 401)" - the token is wrong or was regenerated.
    In HIMS open this agent, click "Regenerate token", download a fresh
    installer, and re-run it.
  * Agent stays offline - confirm the service is Running (services.msc) and that
    this machine can reach {{.URL}} ; check the log file above.
  * Legacy Windows targets (Win7 / 2008 R2) are collected via WMI/DCOM from this
    agent; make sure the agent host can reach the target's RPC (TCP 135 + the
    DCOM dynamic range).

ADVANCED / MANUAL (not required)
--------------------------------
The agent is a single self-contained executable. Advanced operators can run it
directly without the service by setting environment variables and launching it:
   set HIMS_URL={{.URL}}
   set HIMS_AGENT_TOKEN=<token>
   set HIMS_AGENT_NAME={{.AgentName}}
   hims-agent.exe -console
Building from source is only for developers and is documented in the HIMS repo
(deploy/build-agents.ps1). Operators should use this installer.
